The paper deals with classification problems and proposes a method to train deep neural networks without explicit human annotations. This falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the noise generated during the label collection process, which is a common problem in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions the use of natural language processing techniques to generate candidate labels, which is a topic in computational linguistics (cs.CL).
